    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 1.7: VEHICLE FEATURES - OPTIONAL FEATURES -
        CRUISE CONTROL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="f1900702" svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CRUISE CONTROL</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1900703">1.30</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the cruise control switches.
        </para>
        <para>This feature provides vehicle speed using automotive style On, Off, Set/coast, Resume/Accel, switches.
            Speed control is disabled when the service brakes are applied, the clutch pedal is depressed or an automatic
            transmission is placed in neutral. The accelerator pedal can be used to provide a speed increase from the
            cruise speed selected.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1900703" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1209" filename="../figeg1/EG1209.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 1.30 Cruise Control Switches</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
